{"key":"post-10733612","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10733612</id>\n<content>Coffee and coir are about equal as far as bulk growing goes.&amp;nbsp; Mixed together with verm is a great combination.&amp;nbsp; Those who think the pH of coffee grinds is off are mistaken.&amp;nbsp; Coffee grinds are about a pH 6.5 or so, which is perfect.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Oysters grow well on 100% coffee grinds, but cubensis benefits from either manure or coir mixed in with the coffee.&amp;nbsp; If you have coir and verm, mix it with your coffee in about even amounts.&amp;nbsp; Add gypsum at up to ten percent of the amount of coir and coffee for an extra boost.&amp;nbsp; Don't worry about adjusting the pH.&amp;nbsp; It will be in the correct range with those ingredients.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10733627</next>\n<prev>10733577</prev>\n<first>10722008</first>\n<last>10737190</last>\n<when>1248470174</when>\n<utime>07/25/09 12:16 AM</utime>\n</post>"}